    "title": "Bound memory usage when recovering from a crash during chainstate write",
    "body": "Now that #10148 is merged, it's possible to exceed configured memory limits for the utxo cache while recovering in `ReplayBlocks`.  We should fix this, perhaps by making the recovery itself use non-atomic writes:  https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/10148#issuecomment-310473040\r\n",
